<p>Back in 1775, it was the several states that refused to comply with royal edicts, and it was the leaders of state government that gave form and substance to the revolutionary inclinations of the people.  Here&#8217;s hoping that we can still muster a few men of wealth and substance who will stand against the political crowd and provide a core of leadership.  Men such as Ron Paul, but within state government.</p>
